title._content: Lieutenant Adolphus August Frederick FitzGeorge, of H.M.S. Galatea, 1868 / photographer Montagu Scott of Sydney

description._content: Viewers might be surprised to discover that Alfred, Duke of Saxe-Coburg and Gotha, commander of Galatea, was not the only royal to visit Australia in 1867-1868. Lieutenant FitzGeorge was the second son of HRH Duke of Cambridge and an actress, and a great grandson of George III, and so was a second cousin to Alfred, who was the second son of Queen Victoria. FitzGeorge was not entitled to any royal prerogatives or titles. He became a rear admiral in the Royal Navy later. Wikipedia biography of FitzgGeorge: en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adolphus_FitzGeorge Format: Photograph Notes: Find more detailed information about this photograph: acms.sl.nsw.gov.au/item/itemDetailPaged.aspx?itemID=886784 Search for more great images in the State Library's collections: acms.sl.nsw.gov.au/search/SimpleSearch.aspx From the collection of the State Library of New South Wales www.sl.nsw.gov.au
